&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Abacus Nursery and Holiday Club&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Supply Childcare Practitioner/Play-worker, Band 2; As and When Required.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Abacus Nursery provides day care for children aged from 3 months through to 5 years. We also operate a Holiday Club, based at the Nursery, for Children aged 4 – 14 years. The ability to work as part of a team and a commitment to providing high quality childcare is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for motivated, enthusiastic, reliable and adaptable childcare workers to come and join our team of supply childcare practitioners to work in the nursery/holiday club as and when required.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;These should be adaptable, flexible Childcare Practitioners who have some experience of working with pre-school children or with children aged 4 – 14 years. Work may include anything from full-time to occasional day/morning/afternoon to cover sickness/annual leave, also suit students looking for holiday work.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information, please contact Samantha Orange, Nursery Manager, Abacus Nursery on 01924 543039. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Mid Yorkshire Hospitals NHS Trust is an equal opportunities employer and operates a no smoking policy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
